keywords: ["Perovskite", "Solar Cells", "Photovoltaics", "Humidity Stability", "Energy Harvesting"]
abstract: |
  Perovskite solar cells (PSCs) have shown remarkable progress in Power Conversion 
  Efficiency (PCE) but remain sensitive to environmental moisture. This study 
  examine the degradation kinetics of MAPbI3-based cells exposed to relative 
  humidity (RH) levels from 20% to 80%. We find that below 40% RH, the cells 
  retain 90% of their initial efficiency over 500 hours, whereas at 80% RH, 
  rapid structural decomposition occurs within 24 hours.
